{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3b51d1ef-3a9f-4b06-a40c-a6ca2dff5893","content":"**The most likely issue: you need JDK 21, not JDK 17.**\n\nStarting with **.NET 9**, the Android workload requires **JDK 21**. JDK 17 is only sufficient for .NET 8 and earlier. Since it's 2026, you're almost certainly on .NET 9+.\n\n### Fix\n\n1. **Easiest** — let .NET use its bundled Microsoft OpenJDK (unset your override):\n   ```bash\n   unset JAVA_HOME\n   # Remove any JAVA_HOME export from ~/.zshrc or ~/.bash_profile\n   ```\n   The MAUI workload installs the correct JDK automatically under `~/Library/Developer/Xamarin/jdk/`.\n\n2. **If you need a custom JDK** — install Temurin **21** instead:\n   ```bash\n   brew install --cask temurin@21\n   export JAVA_HOME=$(/usr/libexec/java_home -v 21)\n   ```\n\n### Verify\n```bash\ndotnet build -t:ResolveJdkJrePath -v:n | grep JdkJrePath\n```\n\nThis confirms which JDK your build actually uses.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fe131b27-37e4-4d88-b9dc-5b638b987497","outputTokens":293,"requestId":"9BC3:335471:5C5BD71:6797C56:69EC0E61"},"id":"ec5fe928-e3f0-42d3-a76b-315c78fd98d4","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:44:27.613Z","parentId":"cbb3874f-e097-4a74-9ddf-385418ba924c"}
